news.title: UP-RERA establishes division bench for hearing complaints of special nature
news.para: If ten or more allottees of a particular project, association of allottees (AoA) and resident welfare association (RWA) file complaints with the authority, the complaints of allottees of such project will heard by a division bench.

news.title: Jaiprakash Associates lenders appoint Deloitte to support resolution professional
news.para: Lenders had appointed Bhuvan Madan as the resolution professional. Going forward, Deloitte will support the RP, thus replacing PwC, said people with knowledge.

news.title: No ban on stilt-plus-four floor construction, decision up to government: Punjab & Haryana HC
news.para: HC had sought the Haryana govt's response after a realtor filed a petition claiming a stay had been imposed on the stilt-plus-four-floor policy (S+4) policy in the city.

news.title: NGT seeks responses on plea against proposed slum redevelopment in Southern Central Ridge
news.para: NGT stated that the plea raised issues relating to compliance with environmental norms and the implementation of the provisions of the scheduled enactment.

news.title: Bajaj Housing Finance IPO gets 63.60 times subscription on third day
news.para: The Qualified Institutional Buyers (QIBs) part fetched subscribed a staggering 209.36 times while the non-institutional investors quota received 41.50 times subscription. The category for Retail Individual Investors (RIIs) obtained 7.02 times subscription.

news.title: Property prices to surge in Ghaziabad as circle rates hiked by up to 15%
news.para: The steepest hike in the rates will be felt in Wave City and Aditya World City along NH-9 where the circle rate for residential plots will go up from Rs 17,300 per sqm to Rs 35,000 per sqm.

news.title: Arka launches alternative investment fund of Rs 500 crore
news.para: The fund’s first scheme, ‘Arka Hreem real estate opportunities fund I’ (Arka Hreem Fund) has a target size of Rs 500 crore and a green shoe of Rs 250 crore with a focus on residential real estate. It will focus on tier I cities.

news.title: Prestige Estates to use Rs 5,000 crore QIP to reduce debt, acquire assets: Irfan Razack, chairman
news.para: “We plan to allocate approximately Rs 1,500 crore towards debt reduction (and) Rs 1,750 crore for land acquisition,” Irfan Razack, chairman and managing director of Prestige Group, told ET in an interview.

news.title: Bank of Baroda approves resolution plan of Supertech’s Dehradun project
news.para: The company had submitted a project-wise resolution plan in National Company Law Appellate Tribunal (NCLAT) and this is the first project which has got approval from the lender.

news.title: NAREDCO seeks government action on aviation constraints impacting urban real estate
news.para: In bid to help resolve the issue, the developers’ body has made certain recommendations that were discussed during a recent meeting with a Joint Working Group, which included an Expert Committee led by Fali Major, NAREDCO said in a release.

news.title: Odisha hikes ex-gratia amount to Rs 6 lakh for construction workers
news.para: The state government will provide Rs 6 lakh as ex-gratia for construction workers for any accidental death during their employment, said the chief minister.

news.title: China Vanke's bonds tumble as concerns for state-backed property firm mount
news.para: Tradeweb data showed two of Vanke's main bonds due for repayment in late 2027 and 2029 down 2.9 cents and 3.7 cents to 44 cents and 40 cents, respectively.

news.title: Track3D raises USD 4.3 million for business growth
news.para: This investment will drive the adoption of the company's unified reality capture data platform, designed for intelligent, comprehensive, AI-powered construction progress monitoring, it added.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government forms task force to develop Noida into industrial city
news.para: "The idea behind this proposal is to brand Noida not just as an industrial hub, but also as a modern city with cutting-edge urban amenities. The dedicated task force will also identify and develop vibrant cultural spaces within the city," said a govt spokesperson.

news.title: NGT issues notice to authorities on encroachment of ponds by Omaxe
news.para: The green body was hearing a letter petition by a resident, alleging the realtor, Omaxe Limited had encroached upon five natural ponds while developing a residential township, Omaxe City in Lucknow.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM asks officials to resolve land issues and expedite Noida airport work
news.para: The CM, while chairing a review meeting with officials from the district administration, Yamuna Industrial Development Expressway Authority (YEIDA) and the airport concessionaire, said that any issues arising during construction should be resolved at the level of the govt.

news.title: Visakhapatnam civic body to bring 10,000 unassessed properties into tax net in FY25
news.para: The GVMC has identified 4,600 such properties, so far. Additionally, the GVMC has identified 877 properties that were previously underassessed, out of a total of 5,000 properties under review.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body to take over Highland building due to unpaid tax
news.para: On Tuesday, the department stated in a press note that the property tax for the building was overdue as of the 2023-24 fiscal year. Despite repeated notices, the property tax was not paid by the owner/occupant.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body to manage transferable development rights with blockchain
news.para: Traditionally, the AMC has relied on manual processes, including the issuance of development rights certificates (DRCs), approval of transfer forms, and the physical debiting and crediting of TDR. However, the manual system was prone to errors and fraud, senior Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) officials said.

news.title: Over 14 lakh houses built under PMAY in Gujarat in nine years
news.para: Launched by Prime Minister Narendra Modi in 2015, the scheme aims to provide proper housing to the economically weaker sections of society and to the homeless people in rural areas in order to improve their standard of living.
